alert.note: Alert for King (Washington) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued January 21 at 2:01AM PST until January 22 at 3:22AM PST by NWS Seattle
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Washington... Snoqualmie River Near Carnation affecting King County. .Runoff from heavy rain overnight and today in the central Cascades will push the Snoqualmie River at Carnation near flood stage early today. ...FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM EARLY THIS MORNING THROUGH LATE TONIGHT... * WHAT...Minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Snoqualmie River Near Carnation. * WHEN...Until late tonight. * IMPACTS...At 54.0 feet, the Snoqualmie River will flood much of the farm land and several roads from Fall City downstream through Carnation and Duvall. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 1:15 AM PST Friday the stage was 53.2 feet. - Forecast...The river is expected to rise above flood stage to a crest of 54.4 feet late this morning. It will then fall below flood stage late this afternoon. - Flood stage is 54.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 54.3 feet on 01/12/1953. - http://www.weather.gov/safety/flood &&
info.instruction: Motorists should not attempt to drive around barricades or drive cars through flooded areas. Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles. Additional information is available at www.weather.gov. The next statement will be issued by this morning at 1000 AM PST.
